        <p>Irish-born newspaper and magazine editor. BA, Queen’s College, Belfast, 1851. War correspondent for the London <hi rend="italic">Daily News</hi>, 1854–6. Emigrated to the United States, 1856. Studied law and practised briefly in New York, 1857–9. Editor-in-chief, the <hi rend="italic">Nation</hi>, 1865–81. Co-editor, New York <hi rend="italic">Evening Post</hi>, 1881; editor 1883–1900.</p></note>
